Step 3.1 — Pillar G: Goal Decomposition
[NEW] 
pillar_g.py
Metric	How	Source
PPR (Pre-Planning Ratio)	
(time_of_first_prompt - session_start) / total_duration
, scored against 10-20% sweet spot	SESSION_START + first PROMPT timestamps
RC (Requirement Coverage)	tests_passed / total_tests from last TEST_RUN	TEST_RUN events
SOS (Subtask Ordering)	Extract features from CODE_SAVE diffs, check dependency order vs reference DAG, -10 per violation from 100	CODE_SAVE events
DDS (Decomposition Depth)	LLM-as-Judge: provide first 3 prompts, extract subtask nodes, compute overlap with 9-node reference DAG	PROMPT events + LLM call
Aggregate: G = 0.30×DDS + 0.20×PPR + 0.35×RC + 0.15×SOS

