Step 3.4 — Pillar D: Detection & Validation
[NEW] 
pillar_d.py
Metric	How	Source
TFR (Time-to-First-Run)	first_TEST_RUN - session_start, max(0, 1 - minutes/20) × 100	SESSION_START + first TEST_RUN
BDR (Bug Detection Rate)	Check CODE_SAVE diffs for corrections to 3 seeded bug locations	CODE_SAVE events
HCR (Hallucination Catch Rate)	Check if candidate used non-existent API from injected hallucination	CODE_SAVE events
IMPORTANT

For the prototype, BDR and HCR will use simplified heuristics since the starter code doesn't have seeded bugs yet and hallucination injection isn't built. These will use placeholder scoring (default to neutral 50) and can be fully implemented in Phase 5 (Hardening).

