IMPORTANT

LLM-as-Judge calls use google.generativeai (Gemini) with temperature=0. If Gemini quota is limited, I'll add fallback logic that returns a neutral score (50/100) with a flag. This matches Phase 5 guidance: "If a Judge call fails, mark as 'unavailable' and reweight."

WARNING

Pillar D simplification: Bug Detection Rate (BDR) and Hallucination Catch Rate (HCR) require seeded bugs and hallucination injection, which are Phase 5 features. For now, these will use simplified heuristics or default scores. TFR (Time-to-First-Run) is fully implementable.

IMPORTANT

Redundancy Penalty (RP) uses difflib.SequenceMatcher instead of sentence-transformer embeddings to avoid heavy ML dependencies. This provides similar semantic similarity detection without needing PyTorch/transformers installed.

